1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:38,500
=Episode 3=

3
00:01:42,720 --> 00:01:43,880
What are you doing?

4
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:47,200
Taking so many pills
isn't good for your liver.

5
00:01:47,780 --> 00:01:50,680
These are multivitamins to help
prepare my body for pregnancy.

6
00:01:50,830 --> 00:01:52,999
You've been trying
for so long with no results.

7
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:55,040
I thought you'd changed your mind.

8
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:58,040
Well, earlier Xiao Bing had business
dinners and drank with clients.

9
00:01:58,520 --> 00:02:01,220
The doctor said no alcohol for at least
six months when trying to conceive.

10
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,119
Then I came down with the flu,

11
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,799
so we figured we should wait a bit.

12
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,600
But that ended up delaying us
another two months.

13
00:02:07,980 --> 00:02:09,159
You're not even married yet.

14
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:11,320
There's a lot to pay attention to
when preparing for pregnancy.

15
00:02:11,480 --> 00:02:13,320
Of course I have to be careful.

16
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:16,799
You're taking this a bit too far.

17
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:19,879
You're both young and in great shape.

18
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:21,399
Your genes are practically foolproof.

19
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:23,780
There's no way your child
would have problems.

20
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,440
Hurry up.

21
00:02:31,980 --> 00:02:34,120
This is huge, real breaking news.

22
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:35,640
Come inside, let's talk.

23
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,440
What evidence?

24
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:41,800
Don't rush.

25
00:02:44,590 --> 00:02:45,600
Take a look yourself.

26
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,069
Didn't I tell you before

27
00:02:48,070 --> 00:02:48,799
not to eat this?

28
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,999
It'll make you gain weight.

29
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,839
Are you trying to turn into a big bun?

30
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:52,909
If you turn into a big bun,

31
00:02:52,910 --> 00:02:54,159
who's going to like you?

32
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:55,880
No one.

33
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,679
Why are you looking at me? Eat.

34
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,960
Eat this.

35
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,240
This...

36
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,479
Didn't I just tell you?

37
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:03,719
You can't eat that.

38
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:05,720
Why can't you eat this?

39
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:06,839
You child...

40
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,920
Spit it out.

41
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:10,159
Spit it out.

42
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:11,400
Spit it out.

43
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:12,319
Open your mouth.

44
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:14,240
Spit some out.

45
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:15,880
You can't eat that.

46
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:17,840
Tell me, doesn't this count as abuse?

47
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:20,119
Look at how she treats my daughter.

48
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,599
If we give this video to the judge,

49
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:23,600
the child will definitely
be awarded to me, right?

50
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:29,560
What's wrong?

51
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,519
With such strong evidence,

52
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,780
why didn't you bring it out earlier?

53
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:36,720
If you had shown it back then,
wouldn't the court have ruled right away?

54
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:39,519
It just came to me suddenly.

55
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,279
I had no other option.

56
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:43,400
I was going through photo albums at home,
and suddenly saw this video.

57
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,639
It was recorded by accident.

58
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:46,839
That day during dinner,

59
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,960
I went to the restroom
and forgot to stop recording.

60
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,360
Luck was on my side.

61
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:53,359
Alright.

62
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,800
Send me the video now.

63
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:57,640
I'll organize it and send it to the judge,
and push them to schedule the hearing quickly.

64
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:59,040
Okay.

65
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,400
Do you have more like this?

66
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,119
Definitely.

67
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:05,379
I'll go through my old phones
and computers.

68
00:04:05,379 --> 00:04:07,400
If I find similar videos,
I'll send them all to you together.

69
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,639
Send me as many as you have.

70
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:10,919
This case will be solid.

71
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:11,870
Okay.

72
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:17,419
The court lighting is so harsh.

73
00:04:17,420 --> 00:04:19,999
It makes my dark circles look worse.

74
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:20,719
Hey, you there.

75
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,439
Add some warmer light for me later.

76
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,700
Got it, Ms. Lala.

77
00:04:24,780 --> 00:04:25,719
Smile.

78
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:27,490
You look beautiful.

79
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:27,919
By the way,

80
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:29,389
when I walk out from there later,

81
00:04:29,390 --> 00:04:31,319
keep the camera on me the whole time.

82
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:32,559
When I reunite
with my daughter, Xiaolongbao,

83
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:34,519
we'll hug and cry.

84
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:35,999
Then push the shot in,

85
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,159
and give me a close-up.

86
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:38,519
Once the tears fall,

87
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:39,639
that's what the audience loves.

88
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:40,999
That emotional vibe, I get it.

89
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:41,810
Right.

90
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:42,879
Be sharp.

91
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:44,239
If I can't cry later,

92
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:45,799
move the camera away quickly.

93
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,199
What about the music?

94
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,079
Here.

95
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:48,999
Is it ready?

96
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,359
All set. Everything's ready.

97
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,239
"Listen to Mom."

98
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,639
Alright, this one it is.

99
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:53,719
Once the hearing ends,

100
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,519
I'll walk out from that door like this,

101
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:56,599
and cue the music immediately.

102
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,359
Got it.

103
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,239
Perfect, looks great.
Come on, step down.

104
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,520
Alright.

105
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:03,319
Our slogan is,

106
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:04,919
Lala, Lala,

107
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:08,040
leading trends, shining with charm.

108
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:09,079
Okay, let's go.

109
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:10,010
Move.

110
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,240
Have you guys seen it?

111
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,569
The topic about parents
fighting over Xiaolongbao

112
00:05:14,570 --> 00:05:15,969
is trending today.

113
00:05:15,970 --> 00:05:18,109
This morning,
Sun Lala did this makeup look,

114
00:05:18,110 --> 00:05:19,920
the "revenge-for-my-daughter" look.

115
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:22,159
Her live stream
has eighty thousand viewers.

116
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:22,959
I saw it too.

117
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:24,619
I even bought that foundation she used,

118
00:05:24,620 --> 00:05:26,840
the one that lasts through
a twelve-hour hearing without smudging.

119
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:34,360
These people really have no limits,

120
00:05:34,580 --> 00:05:37,800
live streaming right outside
the courthouse.

121
00:05:38,340 --> 00:05:39,270
Look,

122
00:05:39,970 --> 00:05:41,419
you can even see it from here.

123
00:05:41,420 --> 00:05:42,520
Unbelievable.

124
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:44,119
Hello everyone in the live stream,

125
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:46,600
we're now outside the courthouse.

126
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:49,269
- In a moment, it's going to get very intense inside...
- Xiaolongbao.

127
00:05:49,270 --> 00:05:50,400
Dad.

128
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,400
Go, film him.

129
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:53,559
Liu Wenbo,

130
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:54,599
came alone, huh?

131
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,599
So pitiful.

132
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,520
I just checked out your live stream.

133
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:58,919
So quiet.

134
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:01,000
Quiet enough to store winter cabbage.

135
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:03,839
On such an important day, aren't you
going to try and gain some followers?

136
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:05,760
Miss this chance and it's gone.

137
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:07,879
Don't be so smug.

138
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,280
You'll be the one crying soon.

139
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,359
Yeah.

140
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:11,999
I already feel like crying.

141
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,349
Just thinking about what's coming,

142
00:06:13,350 --> 00:06:15,760
a heartfelt mother-daughter reunion,

143
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,720
I can barely hold it in.

144
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:20,800
Keep acting, keep putting on a show.

145
00:06:21,190 --> 00:06:22,279
Come on, turn around, let me see.

146
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:23,480
Where are the tears?

147
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,759
Your team isn't very professional.

148
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:27,599
They should've given you something
to bring on the tears.

149
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,320
If you can't cry, it's all fake.

150
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:30,399
I'm telling you,

151
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,479
once we're in court,

152
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:32,359
I'll tear off your mask.

153
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,680
I've got evidence...

154
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:35,639
What are you saying?

155
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:36,199
Let's go.

156
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:38,159
It's fine, she'll find out
sooner or later.

157
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:39,640
What were you two talking about?

158
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:44,719
Before our emotional reunion,

159
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,079
I'd like to do a quick interview

160
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:46,999
with my ex-husband.

161
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,159
After all, we were once married.

162
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:49,919
After today,

163
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:51,719
he'll be on his own.

164
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:53,879
If you run into him in the future,

165
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:55,479
please be kind,

166
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:57,079
maybe spare him a little help.

167
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:58,880
Alright, thank you everyone.

168
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,999
Thank you to everyone in the live stream.

169
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,039
Sun Lala is not actually

170
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,119
who she appears to be.

171
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,119
In private, she's...

172
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,399
If you want an interview, interview me.

173
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,079
I'm Qin Rui,

174
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,159
from Jindian Law Firm.

175
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,399
Right behind me is Jindian Law Firm.

176
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,640
What are they trying to do?

177
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:11,399
Using public opinion
to interfere with the trial?

178
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:13,200
Call Ma Da, have them removed.

179
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:16,960
Ma Da's a bailiff,
and there's security at the entrance.

180
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:17,999
If you ask me,

181
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,999
our court hearings being live streamed
is what really matters.

182
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,919
The whole process is open,

183
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:23,679
so the public

184
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:25,640
can supervise our work.

185
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,560
What are you looking at?

186
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:37,279
If anyone has cases involving inheritance,
estate division, or child support,

187
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:39,079
- you can all come to me.
- Sorry.

188
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:39,999
No live streaming outside the courthouse.

189
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,400
- Put your phones away.
- Let's go.

190
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:43,279
No streaming allowed.

191
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,680
Go ahead, keep streaming.

192
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,679
That girl is really dedicated,

193
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,919
promoting herself at every chance.

194
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:51,799
Isn't she?

195
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:54,039
Every time I pass the entrance,

196
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:56,279
I see her handing out flyers
and recruiting clients.

197
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:57,840
Even when the bailiffs
chase her off, she comes back.

198
00:07:57,840 --> 00:07:59,319
But this time,

199
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,040
she seems unusually confident.

200
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:03,720
I think so too.

201
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:07,479
Could it be

202
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:09,920
Liu Wenbo really can't have children?

203
00:08:11,110 --> 00:08:12,720
And you guessed right?

204
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:16,520
Or maybe she's already
won over the presiding judge?

205
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,559
There are only three of us on the panel.

206
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,919
Who could she have won over?

207
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:21,560
It's definitely not Jing.

208
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:23,119
Let me make this clear first,

209
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:25,039
I'm completely clean.

210
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,799
I'm upright and incorruptible,

211
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,839
fully committed to upholding justice.

212
00:08:28,840 --> 00:08:31,479
If anyone were a target,
it would only be you.

213
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:32,799
Didn't she report you

214
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:35,720
to the disciplinary
committee three times?

215
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:37,799
Out of three votes,
two decide the outcome.

216
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:39,639
Strict and impartial, no exceptions.

217
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:42,200
What influence could I have on my own?

218
00:08:43,920 --> 00:08:45,480
Let's go, it's time for the hearing.

219
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:47,599
Let's go.

220
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:48,119
Le.

221
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:48,960
Okay.

222
00:08:49,010 --> 00:08:50,240
Thank you.

223
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,440
Please have a seat.

224
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:10,920
(Authorized Representative. Plaintiff)

225
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,720
Court is now in session.

226
00:09:15,760 --> 00:09:17,720
(Hearing in progress)

227
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:21,679
How many times have I told you?

228
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:24,039
No carbs.

229
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,999
Do you want to gain weight?

230
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,360
Spit it out.

231
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,119
You're my little Xiaolongbao,

232
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:31,119
are you trying to turn into a big bun?

233
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:32,129
If you turn into a big bun,

234
00:09:32,130 --> 00:09:33,319
who's going to like you?

235
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,959
No one.

236
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:37,719
Eat this.

237
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,719
Come on, open your mouth.

238
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,199
(Presiding Judge)
Eat.

239
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,599
Stop talking, eat.

240
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,680
Eat, open your mouth. Bite.

241
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:45,840
Swallow it.

242
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:47,239
Open your mouth.

243
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,799
Anything left? Open up.

244
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:49,959
Spit it out.

245
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,459
Spit.

246
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:52,879
Did you spit it all out?

247
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:54,360
Your Honors,

248
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,159
this is newly submitted evidence

249
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:57,559
from my client.

250
00:09:57,560 --> 00:09:59,159
From this video, it is clear

251
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:00,959
that Ms. Sun Lala

252
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:03,120
has engaged in outrageous
abuse toward Xiaolongbao.

253
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,799
How can this be considered abuse?

254
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:05,719
This...

255
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:07,599
At most, it's just disciplining a child.

256
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,199
Is that abuse?

257
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,360
Your Honor.

258
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:11,959
The plaintiff.

259
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:14,440
The defendant not only forced
my daughter to diet,

260
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,959
but to gain online attention,

261
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:17,319
she even enrolled my daughter

262
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,519
in an accelerated piano course.

263
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:21,280
Piano, mastered in two months.

264
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:23,199
Isn't that ridiculous?

265
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,079
After just one month,
she tested the child's progress.

266
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:27,920
One wrong note meant
getting hit on the hand.

267
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:30,440
There was another time,

268
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,960
she signed my daughter
up for a dance class.

269
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:34,919
My daughter
had no dance background at all,

270
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:36,199
and right away it was

271
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,639
splits and backbends.

272
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:38,879
It broke my heart just watching.

273
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:40,799
Those moves could damage
a child's bones and tendons.

274
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,859
What if it affects her growth
or causes injury?

275
00:10:42,860 --> 00:10:45,079
She is simply not a qualified mother.

276
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:45,959
Since the defendant

277
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:46,879
has a long-standing habit

278
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:49,000
of recording her daily life,

279
